flowRoot.flowPara: Friday 17th October
Venue: Science Tower ScB3.31
Massey University, Palmerston North
Registration:
RSVP to pableras.hdez@gmail.com as soon as possible OR fill the google form online. Limited Places.
Travel grants for MacDiarmid Institute affiliates are provided by MESA. First come first serve basis. Register now!
Bring your laptop, with Windows or Mac, and get a fresh install of Ubuntu on it.
We'll guide you to install it using:
A) Virtual Machine. Double click from your operating system to access Linux.
B) Dual boot. Unleash all the linux fun making a partition of your hard-drive, choosing at boot between operating systems (HD backup recommended).
C) Just explore and have fun with a Live CD of Linux, nothing will be installed.
Basic Linux Tutorial during the installation.

flowPara.flowSpan: Discover GitHub, the online platform where the open source happens.
Version control, social coding, interaction, and the fastest community development ever. Also the place to share science-related code, with lot of open projects.

flowRoot.flowPara: Zotero is the open source brilliant solution to have those tons of PDF research papers under control.
EndNote? Mendeley? Explore the open-source, fast-growing alternative to keep a tidy library!
WORKSHOP
Requirements:
Just your laptop -old or new + being registered.
Open for any student, postgrad, or staff. Priority for IFS and MacDiarmid postgrads.
Coffee and tea provided for all attendants.
After the workshop, we are having a BBQ in town that you are invited to --BYO. Open networking, no laptop required.
